description:
Come on our Brew Tour presented by Junket!
Join our Hoppin' Seattle Brew Tour: Presented by Junket! Our Seattle Brewery Tour is a unique experience that offers our guests an opportunity to visit and learn about various breweries and their beer-making processes. This brew tour provides a chance to learn about the history of Seattle and insight into various local ingredients and beer styles. 

Our brew tour combines education, variety, atmosphere, interaction, socialization and local flavors. Whether you're a beer enthusiast or just looking for a fun and engaging activity, our brew tour is sure to leave you with lasting memories and a newfound appreciation for the art of brewing.

review.name: Great coffee tour
review.reviewBody: Our tour guide Zach was so friendly and knowledgeable. We had a wonderful time! I’d definitely recommend if you are in the area!

review.name: Great tour of artisan breweries
review.reviewBody: Great tour of breweries in Ballard, a vibrant Seattle neighborhood which has become the heart of the city’s artisan beer brewing scene. James, who led our tour, was knowledgeable and flexible, the beers (and cider) sampled at each stop were yummy, and really varied. Some walking, flat and accessible. Great experience, highly recommend!

review.name: Great fun
review.reviewBody: This was so much fun!  We walked around and tried several coffees while we heard interesting stories from our guide Zach!

review.name: Great variety
review.reviewBody: Good variety of coffees tasted from cold brew to cappucino.  Zach was the best guide!  Lots of different coffee shops and very informative!

itemListElement.name: Seattle Mariners Baseball Game Ticket at T Mobile Park

name: Seattle Mariners Baseball Game Ticket at T Mobile Park
description:
Nestled in the heart of Seattle with a clear view of the skyline and Mount Rainier on a clear day, T-Mobile Park makes for one of the most picturesque game day settings anywhere in the MLB. The ballpark’s state-of-the-art retractable roof means you will never be rained out—huge win in the PNW!

After breaking their play-off drought in 2022, the Seattle Mariners are an exciting young team on an upward trajectory. That being said, the Mariners are still the only active MLB team to not appear in a World Series. No one can deny the loyalty and hardcore nature of the Mariners support, this is your chance to be a part of the Mariner family and join them on their journey for a World Series title!

The Pacific North West vibe is unique and authentic in the MLB, away from the flashing lights of New York and LA, you will feel the true heart and essence of baseball. From breathtaking nature and scenery to warm, artisan breweries, a trip to Seattle and T-Mobile Park is a baseball purist’s dream!

brand.name: Sports Where I Am - America / P...

review.name: Somewhat disappointed
review.reviewBody: Had seats at ground level first base side; hadn't realized how much meshing interrupts view.  Leaving multistory parking lot takes time, so arrive early to get better spot.  Lots of children, seems quite safe.  I would get seat further up next time.

review.name: Select seats carefully and read bag policy
review.reviewBody:
We paid $40 per ticket and made sure we sat in shade (Seattle has been 29celsius) this summer).  We sat quite high up and behind the batter.- row 15, seat 22 & 22, section 333) - decent view of game.  Unfortunately, one of our seats was broken (big long crack that could catch your skin on leg if not careful). There was no attendant to deal with it.  Would have like to switch seats.  
We didn’t like that people kept getting up to leave for concessions, etc as they would block view of game.  
Strict security policy regarding purses- must be very small ( check their security policy ). I brought a large clear freezer bag to put wallet, bottle of water and some snacks in it).  Didn’t want to purchase a transparent backpack or purse to get thru security.

review.name: Good seats, not cheap but a treat
review.reviewBody:
This was a last minute decision to attend, we were staying nearby and had no idea there'd be a ball game while we were there.  Tickets were simple to download, not cheap but hey, it was a treat.  Security was a bit annoying, I had to buy a clear bag from a vendor (in the UK security still searches one's own bags, no problem!)
The seats we were given were fine, but in fact there were empty better ones nearby so we moved for a better view.
It was our first ball game since we lived in Chicago and attended Wrigley Field regularly, since which time T20 cricket has become our fun, action packed, sporting outing of choice, this was tame and slow in comparison but still a lovely way to spend the early evening

review.name: Great Seats, Pricey
review.reviewBody: Bought Seattle Mariner tickets vs Dodgers. The seats were awesome! Tickets were sent to me via mobile download, easy to access and save in my mobile wallet. Probably could find better pricing for resale tickets, too many fee add-ons  with TripAdvisor.

review.name: Poor experience at a Mariners game.
review.reviewBody:
The ballgame was great!   

But the experience with their parking ramp was  absolutely horrible.  
Who builds a parking ramp that has two identical parking garages but no markings for North ramp or South ramp, no numbers, no distinction in wall colors, NO MARKINGS of any kind to distinguish one side from the other?  
And who thinks it is a good idea to staff it with a guy who thinks it is hilariously funny and smirks at you when you report your car was stolen?  Apparently we are not the first to encounter this.  The attendant referred to it as the Twilight Zone.  We were parked in the South ramp, but coming up the steps from the street to the top level, only the North ramp is visible and we couldn’t see the South ramp where our car was parked at all.  
We had the most stressful 1-1/2 hours of our vacation waiting for the police, thinking our medicines and electronics were gone, and trying to figure out how to get back to our hotel.  
Maybe the “local yocals” knew there were two ramps, but it is seriously inconsiderate to the Mariners guests to have it set up this way.

itemListElement.name: Discover the magic of Seattle (all inclusive 3 hour tour)

name: Discover the magic of Seattle (all inclusive 3 hour tour)
description: This itinerary provides a comprehensive overview of some of the must-see attractions in Seattle, allowing you to experience the city's rich culture, history, and natural beauty in a single day.

itemListElement.name: Meet the Market-Food and Fun tour in Pike Place Market-2 hours

name: Meet the Market-Food and Fun tour in Pike Place Market-2 hours
description:
Tasty Tours invites you to "Meet the Market" and embark on an adventure full of amazing food, history and culture with Supersonic John -A true Pacific Northwest local and the only Market Family tour guide. 

The Market is a 9 acre historic district that can be overwhelming without guidance. Specializing in smaller group sizes Sonic John will lead you through the maze to visit the hidden gems. You will enjoy a wide variety of Tasty exclusive food samples including James Beard award winners, tacos. seafood, pizza and more! Personally meet the craftspeople, vendors and community that make Pike Place Market special. See you soon!

Tasty Tours is permitted and licensed by the Pike Place Market Preservation and Development Authority (PDA) to operate tours in the Pike Place Market Historical District. The PDA requires any business or person conducting paid tours within its properties and in the public areas of the historical district to be pre-approved and to have a license for this activity.

review.name: Overall a good experience
review.reviewBody:
Went back and forth on the rating.

John was really into the market. Seemed like he knew a lot of people there and talked about that a lot. Spent a lot of time on the history of the market and walking up and down the stairs/ramps.

There were some older people in the group that kept getting left behind. He’d roll and just expected everyone to keep up.

We took the tour to sample the food. This is where I’m on the fence. Several of the places have free samples that you could have gotten yourself (dried fruit stand, spice shop). Others didn’t provide anything (o-mart & crumpet shop where we met), and others gave you a huge amount of food - half a pizza slice, 2 Piroshky to split between 3 people. 

I’d taken one of the other tours before in the market and I got significantly less sample size, but it included the cheese store and the chowder shop, and provided something everywhere.

If you want a more in depth tour of the market, this would be the tour for you.

review.name: Tasty tour
review.reviewBody: Not a very large group so it was more intimate and easy to stay together. Lots of info given and tasty treats! I’d take another tour for sure

review.name: My favorite tour!
review.reviewBody: This was a fantastic tour! We had a great time meeting all the different vendors and trying some of their food. John was great, very knowledgeable and friendly. I definitely recommend this tour to everyone!

review.name: Food Tour
review.reviewBody: Chef John was an excellent food guide. Loved the stops and stories that went along with them. One of the best food tours I have been on!!

review.name: Great tour and incredible food.
review.reviewBody: My friend and I with her two boys did this tour on a Wednesday starting at 1030am. The tour was great and John our tour guide was awesome. We tried lots of incredible food and it gives you a really good overview of the market, but I’d recommend going on a Thursday or Friday, since some of the places were closed during our tour. (That might change in April once the cruises pick back up) Other than that, I would highly recommend this tour!
Go meet John Brink! He completed our visit to the beautiful unveiled city. You can get sooooo much out of his tour it’s surprising. History, Facts, Art, Food, Vibes, Laughter. 10/10

review.name: Great way to navigate the Market!
review.reviewBody: Very good tour.  Sonic John is passionate about the Pike Place Market and conveys it's history while navigating the maze!  Very diverse food stops along the way so something for everyone!  A great ambassador for the merchants at the Market - he's like the mayor!

review.name: Kick ass tour!
review.reviewBody: John was awesome! We had a great time throughout the tour. He's passionate in what he does and has all the great tips on all the places to go to. He knows all the ins and outs of the Market Place. I would definitely book with him again.

review.name: Excellent team building activity! John brings the energy and knowledge!
review.reviewBody:
Our Pike Place Market food tour with Chef John was an absolute delight and a true culinary adventure through Seattle's most iconic marketplace. His expertise as a chef really showed in how he curated our tasting experience.

Along the way, we sampled slices of artisanal pizza from DeLaurenti's, biscuits, smoked salmon, a chocolate covered dessert, and more! The tour included fascinating historical tidbits about the market's 100+ year history and insider knowledge of the best vendor spots.

Chef John's connections with the vendors meant we got special tastings and behind-the-scenes insights you wouldn't get exploring on your own. His passion for food and the market's history made this tour both educational and delicious. Highly recommend for anyone wanting to experience the best of Pike Place Market!

review.name: Interesting and tasty
review.reviewBody: I enjoyed learning more about the market and of course, all the tasty samples. And some of the samples were big portions! John was full of energy and very engaging. Part of the fun of this tour was just watching him interact with half of the market as he seems to know everyone.

name: Seattle's Sunset Sail - BYOB!
description: Our Sunset Sail is one of the most relaxing and affordable activities in Downtown Seattle. The Sunset Sail is powered by the wind, so it is extremally Eco-Friendly. We are one of the only cruises in the area that allow you to bring your own beer, wine, and food onboard (Alcohol only allowed for those 21+). Our sailboats were built for racing across the oceans, making them Seattle's most unique Sunset Sail.

review.name: Birthday Cruise
review.reviewBody: We took this cruise to celebrate my 70th birthday and had a great time! We sat in the rear cockpit with Captain Rudy. He and crew know their business and everyone is so friendly. Captain Rudy even let me take the helm, and I steered for the entire cruise! What fun! What a great sailboat. That left Rudy to share many stories with everyone else in back.  Thanks to all, we will do this again, that's for sure!

review.name: Great!
review.reviewBody:
Amazing experience. Would 100% recommend.
I went solo but the crew was very attentive and I didn’t feel alone. Very punctual.

review.name: Wonderful experience!
review.reviewBody: It was a wonderful experience!  The crew was friendly and informative.  The sunset was hidden but the ride was smooth and interesting.   We'd do it again in a heartbeat!!

review.name: from start to finish, was a great experience
review.reviewBody:
fabulous crew and view 

the crew was fantastic and provided a soothing experience with wonderful views of the sound and friendly environment

review.name: End of Summer Sunset Sail
review.reviewBody:
I booked a private sail for a women's group to celebrate the end of summer. It worked out flawlessly on our 70'er with 23 of us comfortably on board.  While there was little wind the crew made the most of it taking us over to Alki Beach and back.  
The boat was clean, crew professional and all around a great night that ended too quickly.  2 hours definitely was not enough!

review.name: Wonderful ending to a fabulous day!
review.reviewBody: Hannah and crew were amazing. BYOB was the best idea….. we grabbed a few beers and snacks. They had coolers with ice to keep them cold. Would highly recommend.

review.name: Sunset at the Sea!
review.reviewBody: It's a pretty good activity to make while you are in Seattle, I really liked the family owned experienced, the captain was cordial and very informative.

review.name: Amazing Unique Experience
review.reviewBody: What a phenomenal experience. It's such a simple and raw experience of sailing, but the crew was fantastic and eager to tell anyone about every aspect of sailing. Our deckhand has been sailing since before she was walking...loved that aspect :-) The heeling of the boat was intense, and so fun to experience compared to seeing it on TV. My wife and I had a beautiful sunny evening and sunset, and that made all the difference. Would highly recommend to do in the middle of summer when you can almost guarantee a sunny evening.

review.name: Wonderful, fun and exciting! Don't miss this!
review.reviewBody:
We had an amazing time and it wasn't too crowded. We were lucky the weather decided to be wonderful and we had smooth sailing.  I checked in an hour early and they told us when to be back and gave us a boarding card. When your number is called you board. 

We got to see the porpoises jumping and the sun setting infont and behind us. We left around 6pm and got back around 8:10pm. There Is a bathroom on board the vessel as well. 

Byob is a wonderful addition if wanted. Other passengers were great as well as staff. 

10/10 reccomend this trip for anyone! Reasonably priced for 2 hours.

review.name: Unforgettable Sailing Adventure in Seattle – Highly Recommended!
review.reviewBody: We had a fantastic sailing adventure! The staff was both accommodating and knowledgeable. We set sail on a perfect early September day, and nothing beats summer on the Seattle waterfront. The excursion was reasonably priced and allowed for spontaneous planning. The crew even let us steer the boat for a short distance, which was a remarkable experience. Plus, unlike many other excursions, this one was BYOB! We brought a delicious picnic and enjoyed some wine. We highly recommend this experience for your Seattle trip!

itemListElement.name: Seattle City Tour with Space Needle and Cruise

name: Seattle City Tour with Space Needle and Cruise
description:
Welcome aboard the Best of Seattle experience with Tripshepherd. Our specially curated journey promises an unforgettable adventure through Seattle's iconic landmarks and unique history.

Our exploration starts with the futuristic Space Needle. Bask in the panoramic cityscape views from this architectural marvel, a testament to Seattle's innovative spirit.

Next, we embark on a scenic city drive, a brief immersion into the city's lively pulse. The journey continues with a serene harbor cruise, a unique opportunity to appreciate Seattle's waterfront. Also we'll stop at Kerry Park to enjoy stunning views of the city skyline, the majestic Mount Rainier, and the shimmering waters of Elliott Bay.

As we traverse the city, we'll cruise by renowned landmarks like the historic Smith Tower, the eclectic Seattle Art Museum, and the bustling Pike Place Market, each contributing to the vibrant tapestry of Seattle.

Join Tripshepherd for this immersive journey through Seattle.

itemListElement.name: Chef Guided Happy Hour Tour - Cocktails, Bubbles and Bites

name: Chef Guided Happy Hour Tour - Cocktails, Bubbles and Bites
description:
Indulge in a delightful journey through Seattle with our expertly guided happy hour walking tour, led by a seasoned chef. Discover the culinary treasures of the city, savoring a variety of delectable items while forging connections with local small businesses and fellow adventurers. It's the perfect blend of exploration, gastronomy, and camaraderie—a must-do experience for any Seattle enthusiast.
This happy hour crawl involves 4 stops for drinks and paired food. We will be walking to each location. IDs are required and will be checked for those enjoying alcoholic beverages.

review.name: Noah is great! We had a fabulous time, learned a lot and really enjoyed the food/drinks.
review.reviewBody: Noah gave us a fabulous tour! He was very knowledgeable and friendly, he fit in so well with our group.  We couldn’t have asked for a better guide.

review.name: Happy Hour Tour with Chef Noah
review.reviewBody: My wife and I had the privilege of going on the Happy Hour Tour with Chef Noah on December 20. We lucked out with a ‘private tour,’ being the only two on it. The tour was like having an old friend share with you some of his favourite spots around the city. The places we went to had an excellent assortment of food and drinks. However, what made it exceptionally fun, was Chef Noah. His interests, love for the city and food, were all infectious. We had an amazing time and really did not want it to end.

review.name: The best tour guide/ food tour in Seattle
review.reviewBody:
Amazing tour with the best tour guide, chef Sean. He was welcoming, knowledgeable and interactive. As Seattle locals, it was still very informative and fun. He brought the 3 couples in the tour together and had everyone laughing from the first stop till the end. 
I look forward to trying the other Seattle eats tours with chef Sean.

review.name: Really fun
review.reviewBody: This was a really fun tour. We had a lot of delicious food and drinks. The tour guide was interesting and knowledgable. I liked the small group size.

review.name: Take this tour!
review.reviewBody: We had a great time touring with Chef Noah. He was very knowledgeable on Seattle food, history and culture. The spots we visited were all delicious and accommodating. Highly recommend taking this tour! At the end, we learned it was Noah’s first happy hour tour and we would have never know it! ♥️

review.name: Excellent Tour w/ Local Flavor & Camaraderie
review.reviewBody: Our tour guide Sean was awesome! We did the day tour and happy hour. Great insights on local history and hideaway spots we wouldn’t have known existed. Liz, the owner, was very communicative on changes with the day tour and Sean still did the happy hour, even though others rescheduled and it was just me and my husband. Highly recommend and will do again next time we’re in town!

review.name: Fantastic Happy Hour Tour
review.reviewBody: This tour was an absolute blast! The drinks and bites were all excellent! Sean did a great job of molding the tour to the vibes of the group, and we got to learn a lot while still having a great time. Absolutely recommend!

review.name: Hidden gems in SLU with THE BEST tour guide!
review.reviewBody: The South Lake Union happy hour tour was amazing! The pace of the tour was fantastic where I didn’t feel rushed, and also felt like we spent the perfect amount of time at each place. We went to a lot of hidden gems in an area that doesn’t see a lot of foot traffic on the weekends, and I now know some pretty amazing food and drink places in SLU. Sean is a fantastic tour guide where you immediately feel welcome and comfortable with how personable and kind he is. This is truly an amazing tour, and I truly hope more people get to experience it!

review.name: Do yourself a favor and go on this Happy Hour Tour!!! ☺️
review.reviewBody: Seriously the BEST happy hour tour for not only tourists but for locals as well. I learned of some of the best happy hour spots to hit up (and as a local I’ll def be going to these places for happy hour, glad that I got the inside scoop into my city). Cocktails are awesome, food is awesome, and our tour guide, Sean, also is so fun and knowledgeable about food, drinks, and the city of Seattle!! I can’t recommend this tour enough!! I was so consumed with having a good time that I only snapped a couple of photos!

review.name: So much fun!
review.reviewBody: Whether you’re a local or visiting you have to give this tour a shot! Chef Sean was so knowledgeable and fun. Lots of new places I’ve never been to with delicious drinks and bites.

itemListElement.name: Eat Around the World Seattle Food Tour

name: Eat Around the World Seattle Food Tour
description:
This Seattle food tour is unlike any other, tapping into the rich history and cuisine of the Chinatown International District. Come join a local guide to experience flavors from around the world, all located within one unique neighborhood!

Your Seattle foodie tour include tastes from all over the globe, from Japanese festival foods to Filipino-inspired treats. You may enjoy tea from a historic hotel and navigate an Asian supermarket for a special snack with your tour guide. Perhaps we’ll stop by an Asian bakery or a restaurant serving up traditional Chinese staples.

Along the way, you’ll learn about the history and origins of Seattle’s International District, and your Seattle walking tour may pass by some important landmarks, including the Chinatown gate and beloved historic restaurants and museums. You’ll also pass by modern-day sites that have supported the community for decades.

Come hungry: we plan to fill you up while supporting our local businesses on this food tour adventure!

review.name: Loved this Seattle food tour
review.reviewBody: Excellent and fun tour of Chinatown and Japantown. We had 5 or 6 stops and got to try dim sum, malasadas, musubi, taiyaki, takoyaki and tea. Loved all the choices! I found out that our guide, Lee, does other tours and I wish we had more time to take them. He was knowledgeable about the history of the area and was engaging and friendly. I highly recommend this tour! Just do it!

review.name: Embrace this beautiful neighborhood
review.reviewBody: Wanted to “play tourist” in the city that I moved to. I had always wanted to explore this neighborhood and Lee was an amazing guide. Everything we ate was incredible and it wasn’t just food, Lee is extremely knowledgeable of the communities and their history and impacts to Seattle. It’s a really lovely tour for anyone visiting or even locals who want to embrace their city. He even gave a great bar recommendation after it ended. Couldn’t recommend more.

review.name: Delightful, personable, and delicious experience
review.reviewBody: My niece and I enjoyed a fun, informative, and delicious tour through Chinatown-International District with our guide Lee! He was friendly, knowledgeable, and certainly has a passion for what he does. Highly recommend this tour— and bring your appetite!

address.streetAddress: 6056 Martin Luthur King Jr. Way South

itemListElement.name: Seattle to Leavenworth Private 8 Hour Private Driving Tour

name: Seattle to Leavenworth Private 8 Hour Private Driving Tour
description:
Enjoy a completely private driving tour from Seattle to one of Washington State’s top destinations, the Bavarian village of Leavenworth!

Your tour starts with a two to two-and-a-half-hour drive through the stunning Cascade Mountains and during which your guide will get to know you while you get to know the natural and early human history of the beautiful Pacific Northwest.

You’ll soon find yourself in Bavaria, or somewhere very much like it! With your guide, you’ll enjoy a Leavenworth tour, featuring alpine German-style buildings, charming streets, and beautiful views of the surrounding mountains. Take some time to dine at a German-style restaurant based on your guide’s recommendations and enjoy shopping at one of the many boutique businesses, including an all-year-round Christmas store!

With a private driving tour from Seattle, you’ll have some flexibility to maximize your time in Leavenworth or spend it exploring other attractions along the way!

itemListElement.name: Whidbey Island 8 Hour Private Driving Tour

name: Whidbey Island 8 Hour Private Driving Tour
description:
Whidbey Island is the perfect day trip to experience the beauty of western Washington. On your private driving tour from Seattle, you’ll travel through forest, field, and water for unforgettable scenic views, quaint island towns, and iconic Pacific Northwest nature. 

Your Whidbey Island tour starts with a drive and ferry ride (time and availability may vary) from Seattle. Once there, we’ll visit charming towns situated high on the island’s coastal bluffs and where you can explore, shop, and grab lunch.

The island has several natural areas where we can stretch, spot some wildlife, and enjoy incredible views. We can include a tour stop at a historic state park, a picturesque lighthouse, and a farm serving up a specialty of the island, marionberry pie!

You won’t want to miss Whidbey’s top tour attraction, Deception Pass. Brave the 180-foot-high bridge walkway or enjoy exceptional views from below. After a full day of sightseeing, sit back, relax, and enjoy the ride back to Seattle.

itemListElement.name: True Crime and Tragedy in Victorian Seattle Walking Tour

name: True Crime and Tragedy in Victorian Seattle Walking Tour
description:
True Crime and Tragedy in Victorian Seattle is our most popular tour program! Explore Seattle's historic Lake View and take a journey into the past through an array of stories of true crime and tragedy in the city's early decades. Life was tough in Victorian era Seattle and often ended quite unpleasantly. 

Learn how Seattle's pioneer generations survived...or didn't...under the constant cloud of unexpected death and tragedy. Real stories of real people drawn from Seattle history from the 1870's through the early 1900s. 

Sensational murders, axe wielding killers, shipwrecks, desperate family tragedy, gory accidents...this tour has a bit of everything. 

(***Note -this tour takes place in historic Lake View Cemtery in September and October - NOT in Pioneer Square****)

itemListElement.name: Events At Four Seasons Hotel Seattle

name: Events At Four Seasons Hotel Seattle

itemListElement.name: Seattle History Tour with Skyline Views Small Group Tour

name: Seattle History Tour with Skyline Views Small Group Tour
description:
Come join us on a historic tour through Pioneer Square and pair it with one of the best things to do in Seattle: see the city from 35 floors up! 

Your Seattle tour starts with a walk through the historic neighborhood, where you’ll easily be able to imagine the city’s early pioneer days with the help of your local tour guide. Top Seattle attractions we’ll pass by include Klondike National Historical Park, Waterfall Garden Park, and the Seattle waterfront. 

As you take in the neighborhood’s charm and architecture, your Seattle guide will narrate the fascinating history of the area, from indigenous settlement to Pacific Northwest pioneer town. Learn the surprising background of the city’s founding, immigrant influence, and the vice that gave this neighborhood a certain reputation. 

We’ll then take our tour above the streets to enjoy incredible 360-degree views of Seattle, the Sound, and the distant mountains from Smith Tower, a stunning building with a fascinating history of its own!

review.name: Awesome tour with Sam
review.reviewBody: Sam was an excellent guide! We learned so much about Seattle and loved his personal passion for the city and its history. Very entertaining- would recommend to anyone wanting to learn about Seattle’s history.

review.name: Great Tour with an amazing guide!!
review.reviewBody:
Great historical tour… our guide Sam was amazing, his knowledge of the area was outstanding. He was friendly and informed and happy to take time to answer our questions. We were extremely lucky as there were just the two of us on his tour this morning, so we got to take it at our own pace with Sam’s undivided attention…. We came away with so much knowledge of Seattles history… Who knew how quickly it grew! And how many companies grew from humble beginnings!! Sam was very sensitive to include what the growth meant to the indigenous peoples of the region, which we appreciated as it often gets missed from the history books… we ended up oat the top of Smiths Tower, with great views of the area and beyond… Thank you Sam for your recommendations during our flying visit!! 
If you’re thinking of doing this type of tour, don’t hesitate it’s a couple of hours well spent

review.name: Great Saturday afternoon/evening tour in Seattle
review.reviewBody: Great historic tour with William who has seemingly limitless knowledge of the city and its deep history. The tour concluded at the top of Smith Tower with an amazing view of the city. William was very friendly and also took so many of our questions that just added to the experience.

review.name: Enjoyable stroll through a less than normal neighborhood.
review.reviewBody: Very sweet tour guide, very knowledgeable. Knows the city well. His nervous charm was fantastic. Got to see a side of this area that I have not seen before. Landmarks I had walked by things that Will gave value to and corrected history that I never knew. Amazing. Thank you.

review.name: Great views of the city.
review.reviewBody: It was a great tour. William was very knowledgeable.   Walking around the city and then going up in Smith's Tower was awesome. I've been to Seattle numerous times, but this was a completely different experience.

review.name: Very informative tour
review.reviewBody: Very informative, not rushed. Very friendly guide who answered all of our questions and even stayed a little longer to make sure we saw everything at the smith tower.

review.name: Absolutely awesome
review.reviewBody: William was absolutely awesome. The tour was a highlight of our time in Seattle. Can’t thank William enough for showing us this beautiful city.

review.name: Seattle history
review.reviewBody: Our guide Sam was really nice. We loved to know all about the Seattle history. Even in a cloudy day we cold enjoy a nice  view from the top of the Smith Tower.

review.name: Tolle Privatführung
review.reviewBody: Wir hatten das große Glück, dass unsere Tour nur zu dritt besetzt war, und wurden bestens über alle unsere Fragen informiert. William hatte auf jede Frage eine sehr detaillierte Antwort, so viel Glück hat man selten

review.name: Be in the know when you go!
review.reviewBody: William conducted this tour for my husband and granddaughter and me. It’s obvious he loves his hometown of Seattle and did a fine job of sharing stores and history and anecdotes with us! We won’t soon forget Skid “Road” and I particularly loved seeing the Raven Skyriver blown glass “carved” sculptures and hearing about the Gold Rush and Native American influences. William definitely helped us understand how and why Seattle grew and bettered itself over the last 175 years. The walkthrough of Smith Tower exhibits, art deco and ornate embellishments and the capstone outside balcony walk around the building’s 35th floor observatory was awesome! What a vantage point of wharf, Mt. Rainier, and the Seattle skyline! Finally we sincerely thank William for so kindly finding some water mid-tour for us unequipped and dehydrating tourists.

itemListElement.name: Artistic Seattle with Self-Guided Audio Tour

name: Artistic Seattle with Self-Guided Audio Tour
description:
Welcome to Seattle, a city that treats to an intricate array of the giant public artworks scattered at every step. Art lovers will be delighted to experience it!

Compose your own music while walking through the huge flower sculptures. Learn why Seattleites don’t carry umbrellas despite the city's rainy reputation. Discover popular public art pieces of different styles, forms, and colors. Feel a nostalgic atmosphere at the first Starbucks coffee shop. Enjoy the glorious waterscape of the Puget Sound and the Olympic Mountains.

The mobile app helps you explore Seattle with a private audio tour (included). All you need is a mobile phone. Download tours in advance to listen without WiFi.

The audio guide on the mobile app is the best way to enjoy the tour at your own pace. WeGoTrip app is available on the App Store and Google Play and works offline.

Join the tour and get ready to explore Seattle's urban art scene that makes the city so unique and cozy!
